  "texts": [
    "We use the encoding scheme proposed in [13], with L levels of increasing frequency:γ(x) = [sin(2 0 πx), cos(2 0 πx),... sin(2 L-1 πx), cos(2 L-1 πx)] Activation FunctionsSpectral bias can also be overcome by replacing the commonly used ReLU with an alternative activation function.",
    "A common strategy is the use of sine activation functions in sinusoidal representation networks (SIREN) [10].",
    "The input to this activation function is scaled by a factor ω 0, i.e., α(z) = sin(ω 0 z).One drawback of SIREN is the bias towards a particular subset of frequencies.",
    "Flexible spectral-bias tuning in Implicit Neural Representation (FINER) [11] adjusts the SIREN activation function to α(z) = sin(ω 0 (|z|+1)z) to overcome this.",
    "Here, the frequency of α(z) increases with |z|."
  ],
